headline: Ameriprise Financial (AMP): Net Margin Slips, Slower Earnings Growth Challenges Bullish Narrative
summary: Ameriprise Financial (AMP) posted a net profit margin of 17.7%, slightly below last year’s 18.1% margin. The company's earnings grew by 5.1% over the past year, falling short of its 14.3% annual average over the last five years, and forecasts show both revenue and earnings growth will trail the broader US market. Still, with shares trading well below industry price-to-earnings ratios and analyst price targets, investors are looking at Ameriprise as a value play, supported by recent profit and...
